the [[Premier League]]; initially on loan from [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/657626/artikel_hadergjonaj-wird-ein-schanzer.html|title=Hadergjonaj wird ein Schanzer|first=kicker, Nürnberg,|last=Germany|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2017/august/loan-florent-hadergjonaj-joins-htafc/|title=Huddersfield Town LOAN: FLORENT HADERGJONAJ JOINS HTAFC|access-date=2017-08-24|language=en-gb}}</ref> Hadergjonaj signed a three-year contract in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43327734}}</ref>
==Club career== Hadergjonaj is a youth exponent from [[BSC Young Boys]]. He made his [[Swiss Super League]] debut on 29 September 2013 against [[FC Zürich]] in 0–1 home defeat.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/09/29/switzerland/super-league/bsc-young-boys-bern/fc-zurich/1481227/|title=Young Boys vs. FC Zürich - 29 September 2013 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2014-08-26}}</ref> He made 11 league appearances during the 2013–14 season. He won the BSC Young Boys player of the year award after 1 year and a half from his debut.
On 8 August 2016, Hadergjonaj penned a four-year deal with FC Ingolstadt 04.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hadergjonaj zu Ingolstadt, Joss zurück zu YB|url=http://www.bernerzeitung.ch/sport/fussball/joss-kehrt-zu-yb-zurueck-hadergjonaj-geht-zu-ingolstadt/story/16133181|publisher=Berner Zeitung|accessdate=29 August 2016|language=German|date=8 August 2016}}</ref>
On 24 August 2017, Hadergjonaj was signed on a season long loan by [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], with the club purchasing the young Swiss during the January transfer season (2018).<ref name=":0" />
